edu.ucdavis.cstars.client.tasks

Class Address

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
      • edu.ucdavis.cstars.client.tasks.Address

  • public class Address
extends com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
    The address argument is data object that contains properties representing the various address fields accepted by the corresponding geocode service. These fields are listed in the addressFields property of the associated geocode service resource. For example, if the addressFields of a geocode service resource includes fields with the following names: Street, City, State and Zone, then the address argument is of the form: { Street: "", City: "", State: "", Zone: "" } Locators published using ArcGIS 10 or later support a single line address field which can be specified using the following syntax: var address = {"Single Line Input":"380 New York St, Redlands, CA 92373"}; Services Directory can be used to find out the required and optional address fields.
    Author:
    Justin Merz
